1 - a\cdot \frac{\partial z}{\partial x} - b\cdot \frac{\partial z}{\partial y} + (ab-ab)\cdot \frac{\partial z}{\partial x}\cdot \frac{\partial z}{\partial y} \equiv 0
a\cdot \frac{\partial z}{\partial x} + b\cdot \frac{\partial z}{\partial y} = 1
